<h1>To Adam Stephen</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<p style="text-indent: 0;">To Lt Colonel Stephen.</p> 
<p style="text-indent: 0;"><span style="float: left;">Sir</span><span style="float: right;">[Fort Loudoun] April 24th 1758.</span></p>     
<p style="clear: both;">I have this instant, and not before, received Orders from the President to complete the Regiment under my command.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> But, as no money is yet come for that salutary purpose, I am at a loss how to act. However, that no time may be lost, or blame laid at my <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">door</span>; I desire that you will send as many officers on this Service as can be spared from your <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">command</span>; and let them recruit about Fredericksburgh and the parts adjacent.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> You will no doubt take care to direct them, to enlist such men as will not finally be refused. Let the officers give a little advance, and an order upon me for the balance of the levy-money, to each recruit; which shall be paid to them immediately upon their arrival. They are to enlist upon the same footing with the new-raised regimentwith this advantage, to the recruitthat he will receive clothing immediately upon his coming here.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> For other necessary directions I must rely on you; being extremely hurried and not able (therefore) to write fully to you at this time.</p>
<p>I entreat you to forward a letter herewith sent, to the President, with the utmost expeditionnot one moment should be lost.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0004-ptr">4</a> I am, Sir, Your most obed. Servant,</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">G:W.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>John Blairs orders are missing, but see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0103&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-05-02-0103-fn-0001#GEWN-02-05-02-0103-fn-0001" class="document">GW to Blair, 24 April, n.1</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For Stephens arrival in Fredericksburg, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0100" class="document">Stephen to GW, 22 April</a>. Lt. Walter Steuart of Stephens command presented to GW a receipt dated 26 April for 10 that he had paid to a recruit at Fredericksburg, and Lt. John Blagg, also of Stephens command, recruited at least twenty-two men probably in and around Fredericksburg (see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0135" class="document">Blagg to GW, 11 May</a>).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>The terms for enlistment are set out in 7 <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William Waller Hening, ed. &lt;i&gt;The Statutes at Large; Being a Collection of All the Laws of Virginia, from the First Session of the Legislature, in the Year 1619&lt;/i&gt;. 13 vols. 181923. Reprint. Charlottesville, Va., 1969. ]">Hening</span> 16369. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0099&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-05-02-0099-fn-0001#GEWN-02-05-02-0099-fn-0001" class="document">GW to Andrew Lewis, 21 April, n.1</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0105-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0103" class="document">GW to John Blair, 24 April</a>.</p>

</div>
</div>
